52
00:02:09,330 --> 00:02:12,260
would always be worth the same amount to the
dollar.

53
00:02:12,260 --> 00:02:14,450
From 1994 through 2004,

54
00:02:14,450 --> 00:02:17,750
it was 8.26 yuan equals 1 dollar.

55
00:02:17,750 --> 00:02:21,060
Now, other countries have fixed exchange rates
too.

56
00:02:21,060 --> 00:02:24,159
The issue is that as China's economy grew
rapidly,

57
00:02:24,159 --> 00:02:28,069
the central bank kept their yuan fixed at
the same low rate,

58
00:02:28,069 --> 00:02:30,939
so it was worth less than it should have been.

59
00:02:30,939 --> 00:02:35,519
Which meant that Chinese-made stuff was artificially
cheaper.

60
00:02:35,519 --> 00:02:37,159
So more and more American companies

61
